At about 12.30 am on Friday 28 July 1985, a group of 12 pupils from Bishop Fox's School, Taunton, visited Pyleigh Manor Farm, near Bishop's Lydeard, Somerset. The owner of the farm is Mr. Mark Day, a polite, well-spoken gentleman in his late 60s. He welcomed the school group and showed them around his farm.
The first port of call was the milking parlour. Mr. Day showed the children how the cattle were milked every day and explained the function of each item in the parlour. Today cattle are milked more quickly and hygienically than at any time in the past.
